item.description: On the season 1 finale of Netflix's new hit reality show, The Ultimatum, viewers got to see where the couples are these days. Fans were particularly curious about what happened to Jake Cunningham and Rae Williams who decided to travel the world together after splitting with their original partners, April Marie and Zay Wilson. Jake and Rae hit it off from the start. Everyone in the cast except their partners thought that they should leave the experiment together — which they did.

item.title: 10 Netflix Originals Nobody Likes (And 10 Everyone Loves)
item.description: Quick LinksNobody Likes: Girlboss Everyone Loves: Orange Is The New Black Nobody Likes: Iron First Nobody Likes: Fuller House Everyone Loves: Stranger Things Nobody Likes: Marco Polo Everyone Loves: House Of Cards Nobody Likes: Haters Back Off Everyone Loves: 13 Reasons Why Nobody Likes: The OA Everyone Loves: Unbreakable Kimmy Schmidt Nobody Likes: Hemlock Grove Everyone Loves: Jessica Jones Nobody Likes: Sense8 Everyone Loves: Daredevil Nobody Likes: The Ranch Nobody Likes: Arrest Development (Season 4)  Everyone Loves: Master Of None Everyone Loves: Gilmore Girls: A Year In The Life Everyone Loves: Making A Murderer I love me some Netflix, and I’m not alone.

item.title: Aoki Lee Simmons And 65-Year Old Vittorio Assaf Break Up
item.description: Just days after their relationship went public, it’s been confirmed that Aoki Lee Simmons and her 65-year-old boyfriend, Vittorio Assaf, have ended their romance—that was apparently “never a thing” from the beginning. A source reportedly close to the Simmons family told PEOPLE, “Not only is it ‘over,’ it was never a thing. Aoki is learning to navigate her private life in a public sphere. And that can be difficult. However, Kimora was concerned to see her daughter in that kind of relationship due to what she herself went through.

item.title: Do You Shave Your Pubic Hair?
item.description: Our friend over at Clutch Magazine would definitely like to know. Here’s what she had to say on the subject… My pubescent years must’ve been the best entertainment for my mother. For weeks, I had analyzed, touched, and tried to conceal the black bush that was growing on my vagina. After countless mornings and evenings of attempting to stuff the hair into the creases of my cotton underwear, I eventually stole her cuticle scissors to cut my black grass.

item.title: Gal Gadot Would Give Birth Once a Week' If She Could
item.description: Wonder Woman, indeed! Gal Gadot is reflecting on her “magical” experiences welcoming her three daughters. “I love giving birth,” the actress, 36, told InStyle for its February cover story, published on Tuesday, January 4. “I would do it once a week if I could. And I always take epidurals, to be fair, so it’s not so painful. Just the moment you feel like you’re creating life, it’s incredible.” The Israel native, who shares Alma, 10, Maya, 4, and Daniella, 6 months, with husband Yaron Varsano, noted that pregnancies, however, are “hard” for her.

item.title: Gwen Stefanis Best Fashion and Beauty Moments: Pics
item.description: Gwen Stefani is on a roll! In addition to wowing Us for the last two decades with her vocal prowess, the multi-hyphenate singer, songwriter, mom and designer never ceases to amaze Us with her fearless fashion and beauty sense. Clearly, we’re not alone because it was just announced that the artist will be receiving this year’s Fashion Icon Award at the 2019 People’s Choice Awards — happening Sunday, November 10.

item.title: Lisa Vanderpump's Daughter Pandora Welcomes 1st Child
item.description: Lisa Vanderpump’s new role! TheReal Housewives of Beverly Hills alum announced that she became a grandma on Saturday, November 13, when daughter Pandora Vanderpump Sabo gave birth to her first child. “Obsessively in love with baby Theodore,” the Vanderpump Rules star, 61, wrote via Instagram. “Thank you Pandy and Jason for making me a Nanny Pinky!” The LVP Sangria founder, 35, who wed Jason Sabo in August 2011, also shared a birth announcement on Instagram, revealing that they nicknamed the baby Teddy.

item.title: Potato AirBnB in Idaho Costs $200 a Night: Photo
item.description: No buds about it: This potato house could be yours for about $200 a night! Known as The Big Idaho Potato Hotel, the unusual residence, which is currently available to rent on Airbnb, is a six-ton spud-like structure that was created to promote potatoes across the country. Despite its potato-esque appearance, the abode isn’t actually one giant tuberous vegetable. Instead, it’s made of steel, plaster and concrete, and is currently located in a huge field in South Boise, Idaho, with views of the nearby Owyhee Mountains.

item.title: Craig Counsell Net Worth, Income, Salary, Earnings, Biography
item.description: Craig John Counsell (born August 21, 1970) is a retired Major League Baseball infielder from the United States. During his 15-year MLB career, he was a member of five different clubs. Counsell is best remembered for his postseason performances with the Florida Marlins in 1997 and the Arizona Diamondbacks in 2001. He was awarded the NLCS Most Valuable Player in 2001, and he has been on base for the past two World Series games that have concluded with a walk-off single.

item.title: Dana Mecum Height, Weight, Net Worth, Age, Birthday, Wikipedia, Who, Nationality, Biography
item.description: Dana is the president and creator of Mecum Auctions, which he started with the help of his better half Patti and a couple of dear companions from his kitchen table in 1988. He has now transformed the company into a flourishing enterprise through patience and great enthusiasm for the business. Mecum’s net wealth is largely gotten from his car auction enterprise, Mecum Auction. His enthusiasm for automobile collectibles and muscle cars enlivened him to start Mecum Auto Auction, which is by and by broadcast on Discovery HD Theater.

item.title: How to Dress for Pear-Shaped Bodies
item.description: Us Weekly has affiliate partnerships. We receive compensation when you click on a link and make a purchase. Learn more! We’ve done the research on what looks best for pear-shaped bodies in the past, and have learned there’s one major takeaway: playing up the bust and shoulders to balance out wider hips is the best rule to follow! There are so many ways you can make this happen with cardigans and blazers, which are go-to garments once winter begins to thaw out — and there are other design elements to look for which will flatter your figure endlessly.

item.title: Mo'Nique Still Supports Roseanne Barr, Her 'Sister In Comedy'
item.description: From the looks of things, Roseanne Barr is still on many people’s bad sides for her discriminatory comments about Valerie Jarrett that ultimately cost her a cushy TV job. However, at the very least, Mo’Nique is still in her corner. In a sit-down interview with KTLA, the outspoken comedienne gave her thoughts on why we shouldn’t cancel Roseanne just yet. Mo’Nique insists that even though she said Valerie Jarrett looked like an ape, that doesn’t mean she’s a racist.

item.description: Rumors of an alleged affair between Prince William and Rose Hanbury, the Marchioness of Cholmondeley, have resurfaced amid concerns for Kate Middleton following her January 16, 2024, abdominal surgery. The former model has attended a number of the same events as the royal couple over the years and was even photographed chatting up the duo at a 2016 gathering. However, in 2019, it was reported that Kate and Rose had a falling out, which is what first sparked rumors that Prince William had cheated on his wife with her longtime friend.

item.description: With how many different teams Deion Sanders played on over his NFL career, it makes sense why so few people seem to hate him. From 1989 to 2005, Sanders managed to play for the Falcons, 49ers, Cowboys, Washington, and the Ravens, picking up two separate and sometimes forgotten Super Bowl wins during that time. item.description: Charlize Theron has it all! Well, almost. The gorgeous actress is tall, beautiful, has won an Oscar, and even has an adorable son, but there’s one area she hasn’t mastered.  The A Million Ways to Die in the West star can’t sing a note to save her life. On May 10 she hosted Saturday Night Live, where she reflected on her last time on the show in 2000 when she played a member of the fake Destiny’s Child-esque girl group Gemini’s Twin.

item.title: Fall-Winter 2018 Fashion Week Statement Earrings Trend: Shop
item.description: We’re used to gawking at the clothes on the Fashion Week runways, but the Fall-Winter 2018 season has been all about the bling — specifically, statement-making earrings. On the Saint Laurent catwalk at Paris Fashion Week on Tuesday, February 27, models paired their mysterious top hats with giant ear sparklers that resembled fish bones (super chic ones, of course!) Whether it was the pretty pearl ear cuffs at Prabal Gurung, the ball-chain chandelier designs at House of Holland or the crystal embellished creations at Tom Ford, bold earrings are about to have a moment.

item.title: How Long Has Vladimir Putin Been The President of Russia?
item.description: Among the most important countries in the world, in terms of economic, military and political influence, Russia ranks among the topmost countries in the world. This makes its leader one of the most powerful people in the world. That leader, for a very long time, has been Vladimir Putin, who is the president of Russia. He is one of the longest-serving presidents in the world, leaving many to wonder just how long he has held the position.

item.description: Kelsey Grammer, the renowned actor, comedian, television producer, director, and writer, has an estimated net worth of $80 million. Grammer is best known for his iconic role as Dr. Frasier Crane in the sitcoms “Cheers” and “Frasier”. The duo sparked engagement rumors when Song, 33, was spotted wearing a ring on her left hand while out and about in Beverly Hills on Tuesday, January 25. The Home Alone star, 41, and the Disney Channel alum were first linked in June 2017 after meeting on the set of their 2019 movie, Changeland.

item.title: T.I. and Tiny Sued for Defamation Amid Sexual Assault Allegations
item.description: T.I. and Tiny Harris have been sued for defamation, among other claims, by the first woman to accuse them of assault. Sabrina Peterson, an Atlanta entrepreneur, filed a lawsuit against T.I., born Clifford Harris, and Tiny, born Tameka Harris, on March 1 in the Los Angeles County Superior Court.
